                   "releaseNotes":  [
                                        "Added  native HLS resolver based on the Stream TMDB streaming path",
                                        "Vix resolves TMDB movie and TV episode ids through /api/movie and /api/tv, then builds the signed playlist from the embed page",
                                        "Added flix native HLS resolver from StreamFlix using the Rpmvid encrypted response flow",
                                        "flix resolves TMDB movie and TV episode ids, decrypts the Rpmvid payload locally, and returns ExoPlayer-ready HLS",
                                        "Lowered Android minimum SDK to support Fire OS 6 / older Firestick 4K devices",
                                        "Vix is in the fast native server group, so it appears before slow MP4/MKV probes finish",
                                        "Kept Flix source isolated in Assets; only the compatible resolver behavior was ported into the app",
                                        "Updated core to the new Mew API shape with server=pseudo and disguised HLS playlist support",
                                        "Remote notification JSON fetches now use no-cache headers and a timestamp query to avoid stale GitHub raw config",
                                        "TV Home D-pad Up focus routing is guarded to avoid crashing on TV boxes and Fire TV devices",
                                        "Cascade remains disabled by config and TV stays native-player only"
